  "text": "There was no evidence of high heterogeneity among the studies: I 2 ¼ 20% for men and 0% for women. In the study from Uppsala, Sweden, adjustment for indicators of adult socio-economic circumstances did not alter the estimated associations. [CITATION_1] In one study, [CITATION_2] adjustment for gestational age strengthened the positive association among men. In two other studies, year of birth was included as a covariate. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Non-linearity was assessed in the same two studies, but no evidence of non-linear effects was reported. None of the studies of cancer mortality had adjusted for socio-economic factors in childhood or maternal factors.",
